parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injury or fatality, as the occupants are not protected from the impact.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadvertent deployment of airbags can cause injuries, damage to the vehicle, and potentially lead to accidents.
The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injury or fatality, as the occupants are not protected from the impact.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy or deploy incorrectly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight switch assembly can cause the headlights to turn off or malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights turn off or malfunction when the turn signal is used
headlights do not turn on at all
tail lights and dash lights short out
and the headlight switch feels hot or smells like burning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or die, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. Timing belt failure can also cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs.
symptoms: Engine dies or stalls without warning
loud noise coming from the engine
smoke pouring out of the back and front of the vehicle
vehicle jerks or stalls when driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil burning can cause excessive oil consumption, leading to premature engine wear and potential engine failure. Head gasket failure can also cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs.
Air bag sensor malfunction can cause the air bag to deploy unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries. Air bag deployment can also cause temporary loss of hearing or other injuries.
symptoms: Air bag sensor light remains on
driver sustains temporary loss of hearing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. Idle issues can also cause the vehicle to stall or die.
symptoms: vehicle stalls when turning or stopping.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical issues can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. Cruise control failure can cause the vehicle to lose speed or stall.
symptoms: Speedometer stays on "0" even when tachometer goes up
engine revs at 40 mph but does not speed up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: vehicle cuts off or shuts down at any given time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs.
